44namespace webrtc {
45
46class VideoRtpReceiver : public RtpReceiverInternal {
47 public:
48 // An SSRC of 0 will create a receiver that will match the first SSRC it
49 // sees. Must be called on signaling thread.
50 VideoRtpReceiver(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
51 std::string receiver_id,
52 std::vector<std::string> streams_ids);
53 // TODO(hbos): Remove this when streams() is removed.
54 // https://crbug.com/webrtc/9480
55 VideoRtpReceiver(
56 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
57 const std::string& receiver_id,
58 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>& streams);
59
60 virtual ~VideoRtpReceiver();
61
62 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoTrackInterface> video_track() const { return track_; }
63
64 // RtpReceiverInterface implementation
65 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> track() const override {
66 return track_;
67 }
68 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport() const override;
69 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids() const override;
70 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> streams()
71 const override;
72 cricket::MediaType media_type() const override {
73 return cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO;
74 }
75
76 std::string id() const override { return id_; }
77
78 RtpParameters GetParameters() const override;
79
80 void SetFrameDecryptor(
81 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor) override;
82
83 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> GetFrameDecryptor()
84 const override;
85
86 void SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
87 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) override;
88#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
89 void GenerateKeyFrame() override;
90#endif
91
92 // RtpReceiverInternal implementation.
93 void Stop() override;
94 void StopAndEndTrack() override;
95 void SetupMediaChannel(uint32_t ssrc) override;
96 void SetupUnsignaledMediaChannel() override;
97 uint32_t ssrc() const override;
98 void NotifyFirstPacketReceived() override;
99 void set_stream_ids(std::vector<std::string> stream_ids) override;
100 void set_transport(
101 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport) override;
102 void SetStreams(const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>&
103 streams) override;
104
105 void SetObserver(RtpReceiverObserverInterface* observer) override;
106
107 void SetJitterBufferMinimumDelay(
108 absl::optional<double> delay_seconds) override;
109
110 void SetMediaChannel(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) override;
111
112 int AttachmentId() const override { return attachment_id_; }
113
114 std::vector<RtpSource> GetSources() const override;
115
116 private:
117 void RestartMediaChannel(absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc);
118 void SetSink(rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>* sink)
119 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
120 void SetMediaChannel_w(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel)
121 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
122
123 // VideoRtpTrackSource::Callback
124 void OnGenerateKeyFrame();
125 void OnEncodedSinkEnabled(bool enable);
126
127 void SetEncodedSinkEnabled(bool enable) RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
128
129 class SourceCallback : public VideoRtpTrackSource::Callback {
130 public:
131 explicit SourceCallback(VideoRtpReceiver* receiver) : receiver_(receiver) {}
132 ~SourceCallback() override = default;
133
134 private:
135 void OnGenerateKeyFrame() override { receiver_->OnGenerateKeyFrame(); }
136 void OnEncodedSinkEnabled(bool enable) override {
137 receiver_->OnEncodedSinkEnabled(enable);
138 }
139
140 VideoRtpReceiver* const receiver_;
141 } source_callback_{this};
142
143 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker signaling_thread_checker_;
144 rtc::Thread* const worker_thread_;
145
146 const std::string id_;
147 // See documentation for `stopped_` below for when a valid media channel
148 // has been assigned and when this pointer will be null.
149 cricket::VideoMediaChannel* media_channel_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_) =
150 nullptr;
151 absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_);
152 // |source_| is held here to be able to change the state of the source when
153 // the VideoRtpReceiver is stopped.
154 const rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoRtpTrackSource> source_;
155 const rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoTrackProxyWithInternal<VideoTrack>> track_;
156 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>> streams_
157 RTC_GUARDED_BY(&signaling_thread_checker_);
158 // `stopped` is state that's used on the signaling thread to indicate whether
159 // a valid `media_channel_` has been assigned and configured. When an instance
160 // of VideoRtpReceiver is initially created, `stopped_` is true and will
161 // remain true until either `SetupMediaChannel` or
162 // `SetupUnsignaledMediaChannel` is called after assigning a media channel.
163 // After that, `stopped_` will remain false until `Stop()` is called.
164 // Note, for checking the state of the class on the worker thread,
165 // check `media_channel_` instead, as that's the main worker thread state.
166 bool stopped_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&signaling_thread_checker_) = true;
167 RtpReceiverObserverInterface* observer_
168 RTC_GUARDED_BY(&signaling_thread_checker_) = nullptr;
169 bool received_first_packet_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&signaling_thread_checker_) =
170 false;
171 const int attachment_id_;
172 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor_
173 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_);
174 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport_
175 RTC_GUARDED_BY(&signaling_thread_checker_);
176 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer_
177 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_);
178 // Stores the minimum jitter buffer delay. Handles caching cases
179 // if |SetJitterBufferMinimumDelay| is called before start.
180 JitterBufferDelay delay_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_);
181
182 // Records if we should generate a keyframe when |media_channel_| gets set up
183 // or switched.
184 bool saved_generate_keyframe_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_) = false;
185 bool saved_encoded_sink_enabled_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_thread_) = false;
186};
187
188} // namespace webrtc
189
190#endif // PC_VIDEO_RTP_RECEIVER_H_
